    "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses #7456\n\nThis PR introduces unified `cuda::always_true_t` and `cuda::always_false_t` function object types in libcu++, consolidating the previously scattered definitions across CUB, CUDAX, and test code.\n\n### Changes\n\n- **New header**: `cuda/__functional/always_true_false.h` defines `cuda::always_true_t` and `cuda::always_false_t` structs with variadic `operator()`, plus `cuda::always_true` and `cuda::always_false` inline variables\n- **New compile-time variable**: `cuda::std::__always_true_v` added alongside existing `__always_false_v` for `static_assert` use\n- **CUB unification**: `cub::detail::transform::always_true_predicate` is now a type alias for `cuda::always_true_t`, preserving backward compatibility and CUB's critical `is_same_v` optimization paths\n- **`proclaims_copyable_arguments`** specialized for both new types in `address_stability.h`\n- **Test cleanup**: CUB test files now use the unified types via type aliases instead of duplicated struct definitions\n- **CUDAX STF**: Replaced local `reserved::always_false` with `cuda::std::__always_false_v`\n- **C parallel**: Updated NVRTC kernel name strings to reflect the resolved type\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n1. **Type alias for backward compat**: `always_true_predicate` remains available as a name in CUB via `using`, so existing code continues to compile\n2. **`is_same_v` checks preserved**: Since `always_true_predicate` is now an alias for `cuda::always_true_t`, all compile-time type checks (used for vectorization optimization) work transparently\n3. **Separate concerns**: Runtime function objects (`cuda::always_true_t/always_false_t`) vs compile-time variable templates (`__always_true_v/__always_false_v`) remain distinct, serving different purposes\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] CUB transform tests pass (critical optimization path)\n- [ ] CUB select/partition tests pass with unified types\n- [ ] PSTL algorithms using `always_true_predicate` default work correctly\n- [ ] C parallel NVRTC kernel name resolution works\n",
