      "merge_method": "squash",
      "commit_title": "Unify always_true and always_false into libcu++ (#8708)",
      "commit_message": "* Unify always_true and always_false into libcu++\n\nIntroduce cuda::always_true_t and cuda::always_false_t as canonical\nfunction object types in libcu++, with corresponding inline variables\ncuda::always_true and cuda::always_false. Also add cuda::std::__always_true_v\nas a compile-time counterpart to __always_false_v for static_assert use.\n\n- New header: cuda/__functional/always_true_false.h\n- CUB's always_true_predicate is now a type alias for cuda::always_true_t\n- proclaims_copyable_arguments specialized for both types\n- Updated CUB tests, CUDAX STF, and C parallel NVRTC kernel names\n- Preserves CUB optimization paths (is_same_v checks work via type alias)\n\nCloses #7456\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Address review comments: rename types, remove CPOs, add tests\n\n- Rename always_true_t/always_false_t to always_true/always_false to\n  match std:: functor naming convention (no _t suffix)\n- Remove inline constexpr variable CPOs (not needed for ordinary functors)\n- Remove stale comment about proclaims_copyable_arguments in tuning_transform.cuh\n- Drop :: prefix in test .cu files (use cuda:: not ::cuda::)\n- Update NVRTC kernel name strings to reflect renamed types\n- Add doxygen @par Example sections for both function objects\n- Add unit test (always_true_false.pass.cpp)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Fix clang-format issues in MR files\n\n- Move #include <cuda/__functional/always_true_false.h> to correct\n  include group (cuda/ priority) in test files\n- Break long static_assert line in data_interface.cuh to respect\n  120 column limit\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Address review feedback: simplify docs and split test\n\n- Remove verbose doxygen documentation (Overview, Example sections),\n  keeping only @brief as per libcu++ convention\n- Split single test() function into test_always_true() and\n  test_always_false() for clearer separation\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Address review feedback: remove aliases, use types directly\n\n- Remove `always_true_predicate` type alias from CUB and use\n  `::cuda::always_true` directly throughout CUB, Thrust, PSTL,\n  and C parallel (per davebayer's review)\n- Remove test type aliases (`always_false_t`, `always_true_t`)\n  in CUB test files and use `cuda::always_true`/`cuda::always_false`\n  directly (per davebayer's review)\n- Remove unused `__always_true_v` from `always_false.h`\n  (per davebayer's review)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* [pre-commit.ci] auto code formatting\n\n* Add documentation for cuda::always_true and cuda::always_false\n\nAdd extended API documentation page for the new always_true/always_false\nfunction objects in docs/libcudacxx/extended_api/functional/, and add\nentries to the functional index table.\n\nThis addresses the review comment requesting documentation for these\npublic types.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Address review feedback: add missing includes, fix test headers, update docs\n\n- Add explicit #include <cuda/__functional/always_true_false.h> to all files\n  that directly use ::cuda::always_true (kernel_transform.cuh,\n  dispatch_copy_mdspan.cuh, device_find.cuh, device_transform.cuh, and\n  5 PSTL files: copy_n.h, partition.h, rotate.h, stable_partition.h,\n  transform.h)\n- Remove redundant internal header include from catch2_test_device_select_if.cu\n  (already has <cuda/functional>)\n- Replace internal header with public <cuda/functional> in\n  catch2_test_device_partition_if.cu (tests should not use internal headers)\n- Update CCCL version from 2.8.0 to 3.4.0 for always_true/always_false in\n  docs/libcudacxx/extended_api/functional.rst\n- Remove empty CUDA Toolkit Availability column for both entries\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Use _CCCL_CONSTEVAL for always_true/always_false operator()\n\nThe return value is always a compile-time constant, so consteval\nis more appropriate than constexpr. Update documentation to match.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Revert \"Use _CCCL_CONSTEVAL for always_true/always_false operator()\"\n\nThis reverts commit 8ae1f1bb3a0cf798eb8acde3905c55e021ac0907.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: CodeMate <codemate@nvidia.com>\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nCo-authored-by: AstraCodeMate <AstraCodeMate@nvidia.com>\nCo-authored-by: AstraCodeMate <astra-codemate@nvidia.com>\nCo-authored-by: NVFixit <NVFixit@nvidia.com>\nCo-authored-by: pre-commit-ci[bot] <66853113+pre-commit-ci[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>\nCo-authored-by: Federico Busato <50413820+fbusato@users.noreply.github.com>"
